onna hurt like hell for some time to come.  No getting around that.  Practical advice includes spending time with your friends, talking about it till you don't want to anymore, going anywhere new, seeing something new, just getting the hell out from under.  <br>
<br>
Second, it sounds clear that your girlfriend is gone.  Stuff like this doesn't usually happen without a foundation, and 13 years sounds like shes had plenty of time to figure out if she really wants to be with you forever.  The fact that you went house hunting recently is the real clue.  Nothing like the approach of an actual commitment to shake things loose.  This guy she met on holiday is simply the escape mechanism.  <br>
